aq |work=World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] |accessdate=June 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615131905/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_iz.html |archivedate=June 15, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Jordan}}\n|[[Jordan]] ([[Flag of Jordan|flag]])\n|The seven-pointed star represents the seven verses of the Quran's [[Al-Fatiha|first sura]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_jo.html |title=Flag Description: Jordan |work=World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] |accessdate=June 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615151931/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_jo.html |archivedate=June 15, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Libya}}\n|[[Libya]] ([[Flag of Libya|flag]])\n|[[Star and crescent]] represent Islam<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indexmundi.com/libya/flag_description.html|title=Flag of Libya - Description|publisher=Index Mundi|accessdate=March 23, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Malaysia}}\n|[[Malaysia]] ([[Flag of Malaysia|flag]])\n|[[Hilal (crescent moon)|Crescent moon]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_my.html |title=Flag Description: Malaysia |work=World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] |accessdate=June 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615153925/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_my.html |archivedate=June 15, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Maldives}}\n|[[Maldives]] ([[Flag of Maldives|flag]])\n|White crescent moon symbolizes Islam<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_mv.html |title=Flag Description: Maldives |work=World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|C