ctbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] |accessdate=June 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520091920/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_sa.html |archivedate=May 20, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|Senegal}}\n|[[Senegal]] ([[Flag of Senegal|flag]])\n|The green stripe and star represent Islam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://flagspot.net/flags/sn.html |title=Senegal on Flagspot |publisher=Flagspot.net |date= |accessdate=2014-02-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=8UD0kOEb1XIC&pg=PA198&dq=flag+of+senegal#v=onepage&q=flag%20of%20senegal&f=false|title=Encyclopedic World Atlas|publisher=Oxford University Press|date=December 26, 2002|last=Philip|first=George and Son|page=198|accessdate=May 24, 2013|isbn=9780195219203}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Sudan}}\n|[[Sudan]] ([[Flag of Sudan|flag]])\n|Green represents Islam.<ref name=\"worldflags101\">{{cite web |url=http://www.worldflags101.com/s/sudan-flag.aspx |title=Sudan Flag - World Flags 101 |accessdate=2008-08-09 |author=World Flags 101 |work=WorldFlags101.com |publisher=Moxy Media}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Tunisia}}\n|[[Tunisia]] ([[Flag of Tunisia|flag]])\n|[[Star and crescent]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Turkey}}\n|[[Turkey]] ([[Flag of Turkey|flag]])\n|[[Star and crescent]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Turkmenistan}}\n|[[Turkmenistan]] ([[Flag of Turkmenistan|flag]])\n|[[Hilal (crescent moon)|Crescent moon]] (green may also represent Islam)\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Uzbekistan}}\n|[[Uzbekistan]] ([[Flag of Uzbekistan|flag]])\n|[[Hilal (crescent moon)|Crescent moon]] (green may also represent Islam), the word \"[[Allah]]\" (\"God\") from 12 stars\n|}\n\n===Judaism===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!'''Flag'''\n!'''Country'''\n!'''Religious characteristics'''\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Israel}}\n|[[Israel]] ([[Flag of Israel|flag]])\n|The basic design is based on a Jewish [[tallit|prayer shawl]], the [[Star of David]] is a symbol of Judaism<ref>{{cite web |url