0615130501/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_do.html |archivedate=June 15, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Dominican Republic}}\n|[[Dominican Republic]] ([[Flag of the Dominican Republic|flag]])\n|A [[Bible]], the color white stands for salvation<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_dr.html |title=Flag Description: Dominican Republic |work=World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] |accessdate=June 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615114105/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_dr.html |archivedate=June 15, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|El Salvador}}\n|[[El Salvador]] ([[Flag of El Salvador|flag]])\n| Dios, Uni\u00f3n, Libertad (God, Union, Liberty)\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Fiji}}\n|[[Fiji]] ([[Flag of Fiji|flag]])\n|Crosses of [[St. George]], [[St. Andrew]] and [[St. Patrick]], [[dove]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Finland}}\n|[[Finland]] ([[Flag of Finland|flag]])\n|[[Nordic Cross Flag]]<ref name=\"Jeroen Temperman\" />\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Georgia|name=Georgia}}\n|[[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] ([[Flag of Georgia (country)|flag]])\n|[[Jerusalem cross]]<ref>\"The new flag of Georgia does not seem to be related with this historical banner. The flag of the National Movement was unknown ten years ago [1993] and was called 'the Georgian historical national flag' by the opposition leaders only after publications by the Georgian vexillologist I.L. Bichikashvili.\" Mikhail Revnivtsev, 25 November 2003 [http://www.crwflags.com/fotw/flags/ge.html crwflags.com]</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Greece}}\n|[[Greece]] ([[Flag of Greece|flag]])\n|The cross symbolizes [[Greek Orthodox Church|Greek Orthodoxy]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_gr.html |title=Flag Description: Greece |work=World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]]