8A5%29.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-06 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Cambodia}}\n|[[Cambodia]] ([[Flag of Cambodia|flag]])\n|[[Angkor Wat]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_cb.html |title=Flag Description: Cambodia |work=World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] |accessdate=June 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615142718/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_cb.html |archivedate=June 15, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|India}}\n|[[India]] ([[Flag of India|flag]])\n|The [[Ashoka Chakra]] represents the Laws of [[Dharma]] (righteousness).<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=BmY2nfBmNCgC Flags of the world: an illustrated guide to contemporary flags] Alfred Znamierowski&nbsp;\u2013 2000, {{ISBN|1-84215-337-4}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Myanmar}}\n|[[Myanmar]] ([[Flag of Myanmar|flag]])\n|The color white stands for Theravada Buddhism.\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Nepal}}\n|[[Nepal]] ([[Flag of Nepal|flag]])\n|Based on the Hindu traditional flags.\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Sri Lanka}}\n|[[Sri Lanka]] ([[Flag of Sri Lanka|flag]])\n|The four [[Bodhi Tree|Bodhi tree leaves]] symbolize four Buddhist metaphysical concepts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lankalibrary.com/pro/flag2.htm|title=The Sri Lankan Lion flag -how it came to be |publisher=Virtual Library Sri Lanka}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Thailand}}\n|[[Thailand]] ([[Flag of Thailand|flag]])\n|The color white stands for Theravada Buddhism.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_th.html |title=Flag Description: Thailand |work=World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] |accessdate=June 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615131500/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_th.html |archivedate=June 15, 2013 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Traditional===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!'''Flag'''\n!'''Country'''\n!'''Religious characteristics'''\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Albania}}\n|[[Albania]] ([[Flag of Albania|flag]])\n|The eagle from the Albanian legend, [[The Tale of the Eagle]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Argentina}}\n|[[Argentina]] ([[Flag of Argentina|flag]])\n|[[Sun of May]]'s features are that of the [[Inca]] god [[Inti]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_ar.html |title=Flag Description: Argentina |work=World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] |accessdate=June 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615140823/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/flags/flagtemplate_ar.html |archivedate=June 15, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Japan}}\n|[[Japan]] ([[Flag of Japan|flag]])\n|Red circle represents the sun goddess [[Amaterasu]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Kazakhstan}}\n|[[Kazakhstan]] ([[Flag of Kazakhstan|flag]])\n|Blue represents the sky god [[Tengri]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|South Korea}}\n|[[South Korea]] ([[Flag of South Korea|flag]])\n|[[Taegeuk]] symbol is associated with [[Taoism]] and traditional [[Korean Shamanism]]; [[I Ching]] trigrams.\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Kyrgyzstan}}\n|[[Kyrgyzstan]] ([[Flag of Kyrgyzstan|flag]])\n|The forty sun rays represents forty tribes united by [[Epic of Manas|Manas]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Mexico}}\n|[[Mexico]] ([[Flag of Mexico|flag]])\n|Coat of arms symbolic of [[Aztec]] legend of [[Tenochtitlan]], modern-day [[Mexico City]]<ref name=\"Flag of Mexico\">{{cite web|url=http://www.all-flags-world.com/country-flag/flag-mexico.php |title=Flag of Mexico |publisher=All-flags-world.com |date= |accessdate=2015-07-01}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Mongolia}}\n|[[Mongolia]] ([[Flag of Mongolia|flag]])\n|[[Taijitu]] symbol of [[yin and yang]]. The Sun, Moon and blue colour represent the [[Tengri|eternal sky]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|North Macedonia}}\n|[[North Macedonia]] ([[Flag of North Macedonia|flag]])\n|The sun is based on the [[Vergina Sun]], symbol of the god [[Helios]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Tajikistan}}\n|[[Tajikistan]] ([[Flag of Tajikistan|flag]])\n|The seven stars representing number seven in [[Persian mythology|Tajik traditional legends]], representing perfection and happiness while alluding to a traditional belief that the heavens feature seven mountains and seven orchard gardens with a star shining above each mountain.\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Uruguay}}\n|[[Uruguay]] ([[Flag of Uruguay|flag]])\n|[[Sun of May]]'s features are that of the [[Inca]] god [[Inti]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.all-flags-world.com/country-flag/flag-uruguay.php |title=Flag of Uruguay |publisher=All-flags-world.com |date= |accessdate=2014-02-02}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== National anthems which incorporate religion ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: left\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" | National anthems which incorporate religion\n|-\n!Country\n!National anthem\n!Religion(s) mentioned\n|-\n|{{Flagcountry|Afghanistan|size=23px}}||\"[[Afghan National Anthem|Milli Tharana]]\" ({{Lang-en|\"Afghan National Anthem\"}})||Islam\n|-\n|{{Flagcountry|Albania|size=23px}}||\"[[Himni i Flamurit]]\" ({{Lang-en|\"Anthem of the Flag\"}})||Christianity and Islam\n|-\n|{{Flagcountry|Antigua and Barbuda|size=23px}}||\"[[Fair Antigua, We Salute Thee]]\"||Christianity\n|-\n|{{Flagcountry|Austria|size=23px}}||\"[[Land der Berge, Land am Strome]]\" ({{Lang-en|\"Land of the Mountains, Land on the River\"}})||Christianity\n|-\n|{{Flagcountry|Azerbaijan|size=23px}}||\"[[Az\u0259rbaycan mar\u015f\u0131]]\" ({{Lang-en|\"March of Azerbaijan\"}})||Islam\n|-\n|{{Flagcountry|The Bahamas|size=23px}}||\"[[March On, Bahamaland]]\"||Christianity\n|-\n|{{Flagcountry|Bahrain|size=23px}}||\"[[Bahrainona]]\" ({{Lang-en|\"Our Bahrain\"}})||Islam\n|-\n|{{Flagcountry|Barbados|size=23px}}||\"[[In Plenty and In Time of Need]]\"||Christianity\n|-\n|{{Flagcountry|Belarus|size=23px}}||\"[[My Belarusy]]\" ({{Lang-en|\"We Belarus